e ethnographique.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEthnologyxMethodology. 0aEthnology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh1 aBoudreault-Fournier, Alexandrine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCulhane, Dara, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCulhane, Dara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElliott, Denielle, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aElliott, Denielle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKazubowski-Houston, Magdalena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoretti, Cristina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311127221408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021z978311127464540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782763753744423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9782763753744/original  a978-3-11-127221-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-127464-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles